{"article_id":"rlw0ELlu4LVFmu32","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Obama is considering how to respond to Syrian chemical attack","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"A U.S. strike `` ca n't just be one and done , ''","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"a Middle East analyst says","depth":5},{"id":3,"text":"Few question","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"that there was a major chemical attack in Syria last week ,","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"and the United States has made clear","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"that it blames the government of President Bashar al-Assad .","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"Now , the question is how President Barack Obama will respond .","depth":5},{"id":8,"text":"For almost two years , Obama has avoided direct military involvement in Syria 's civil war ,","depth":7},{"id":9,"text":"only escalating aid to rebel fighters in June","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"after suspected smaller-scale chemical weapons attacks by Syrian government forces .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"However , last week 's attack on a Damascus suburb","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"that reportedly killed and wounded more than 3,000 people","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"obliterated the `` red line ''","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"Obama set just over a year ago against the use of Syria 's chemical weapons stocks .","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"At the White House , spokesman Jay Carney told reporters Monday","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"that Obama was evaluating `` a response to the clear use on a mass scale with repugnant results of chemical weapons , ''","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"adding","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"that `` there is very little doubt","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"that the Syrian regime ... used those weapons . ''","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"Meanwhile , U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry called the attack `` inexcusable '' and `` undeniable , ''","depth":7},{"id":21,"text":"and said","depth":8},{"id":22,"text":"there was `` a clear reason","depth":9},{"id":23,"text":"that the world has banned entirely chemical weapons . ''","depth":9},{"id":24,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"What are Obama 's options for Syria ?","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"What are Obama 's options for Syria ?","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"03:05","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":31,"text":"Taking action against Syria ?","depth":14},{"id":32,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":13},{"id":34,"text":"Taking action against Syria ?","depth":12},{"id":35,"text":"01:40","depth":11},{"id":36,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"The latest from inside Syria","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"The latest from inside Syria","depth":13},{"id":41,"text":"03:39","depth":13},{"id":42,"text":"He said","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"that evidence `` strongly indicates ''","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"chemical weapons were used in Syria","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"and that `` we know","depth":13},{"id":46,"text":"the Syrian regime maintains custody '' of such weapons","depth":14},{"id":47,"text":"and has the rockets","depth":15},{"id":48,"text":"to use them .","depth":15},{"id":49,"text":"Obama `` will be making an informed decision","depth":11},{"id":50,"text":"about how to respond to this indiscriminate use '' of chemical weapons ,","depth":11},{"id":51,"text":"Kerry added ,","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"saying","depth":10},{"id":53,"text":"the president `` believes","depth":11},{"id":54,"text":"there must be accountability '' for those","depth":12},{"id":55,"text":"who use them .","depth":12},{"id":56,"text":"Options","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"available to Obama","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"range from ordering limited missile strikes to continued diplomatic efforts","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"labeled by critics as a `` do-nothing '' approach .","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"Obama will be presented with final options regarding actions against Syria in the next few days ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"a senior administration official said Monday .","depth":8},{"id":62,"text":"Assuming","depth":12},{"id":63,"text":"the president decides to go ahead with a military response ,","depth":12},{"id":64,"text":"any action could come as early as mid-week ,","depth":12},{"id":65,"text":"though it could be later ,","depth":12},{"id":66,"text":"the official cautioned .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"Factors","depth":12},{"id":68,"text":"weighing into the timing of any action","depth":12},{"id":69,"text":"include a desire","depth":13},{"id":70,"text":"to get it done","depth":14},{"id":71,"text":"before the president leaves for Russia next week","depth":14},{"id":72,"text":"and before the administration has to make a decision on whether to suspend aid to Egypt","depth":13},{"id":73,"text":"because of the ongoing political turmoil there ,","depth":13},{"id":74,"text":"the official explained .","depth":10},{"id":75,"text":"The administration also wants it to be a quick response to the use of chemical weapons ,","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"the senior administration official said .","depth":11},{"id":77,"text":"American officials are consulting with allies","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"to ensure","depth":13},{"id":79,"text":"they are supportive of any U.S. action ,","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"which","depth":16},{"id":81,"text":"the senior administration official said","depth":16},{"id":82,"text":"would be very limited in scope and a direct reaction to the use of chemical weapons .","depth":15},{"id":83,"text":"And three representatives of allied governments","depth":15},{"id":84,"text":"involved in those top-level consultations","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"said","depth":14},{"id":86,"text":"the goal is to reach a consensus as soon as possible .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"`` No one is talking about a long process , ''","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"one European diplomat told CNN .","depth":13},{"id":89,"text":"Marie Harf , a State Department spokeswoman , said","depth":12},{"id":90,"text":"any U.S. response would be `` a determination","depth":14},{"id":91,"text":"on how to respond to a blatant use of chemical weapons ,","depth":14},{"id":92,"text":"and it 's not necessarily to change the entire situation on the ground in Syria . ''","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"That might be a mistake ,","depth":12},{"id":94,"text":"said Michael Doran , an analyst at the Brookings Institution 's Saban Center for Middle East Policy .","depth":12},{"id":95,"text":"A U.S. strike `` ca n't just be one and done , ''","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"but should be part of a plan","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"to remove al-Assad ,","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"he told CNN 's `` Anderson Cooper 360 . '' `` The president has been very reulctant to get involved .","depth":14},{"id":99,"text":"Public opinion has been against it .","depth":16},{"id":100,"text":"There 's not a lot of support on the Hill , ''","depth":16},{"id":101,"text":"Doran said .","depth":15},{"id":102,"text":"`` And yet , here we are again .","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"Time and time again , we get dragged further and further in . ''","depth":14},{"id":104,"text":"The result could be `` a Vietnam-type problem ,","depth":14},{"id":105,"text":"where we kind of back our way into this ,","depth":14},{"id":106,"text":"if we do n't come up with a plan","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"about how to win . ''","depth":14},{"id":108,"text":"Kerry spoke with his British , Jordanian , Qatari and Saudi counterparts Monday and with the secretary-general of the Arab League ,","depth":8},{"id":109,"text":"Harf said .","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"`` Obviously , the intelligence assessment is ongoing , ''","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"she said .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"`` But he reiterated","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"that the president is studying the facts","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"and will be making an informed decision","depth":11},{"id":115,"text":"about how to respond going forward . ''","depth":11},{"id":116,"text":"The Obama administration is expected to declassify the intelligence assessment","depth":10},{"id":117,"text":"backing up its assertion","depth":11},{"id":118,"text":"that the Syrian regime was responsible for last week 's chemical weapons attack ,","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"another senior administration official said .","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"The declassification would happen","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"before any U.S. military action would take place .","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"A senior administration official familiar with the intelligence told CNN","depth":8},{"id":123,"text":"that the evidence `` includes","depth":10},{"id":124,"text":"but is not limited to ''","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"satellite images of activity at Syrian military installations","depth":10},{"id":126,"text":"identified as including chemical weapons depots .","depth":10},{"id":127,"text":"Earlier Monday , a White House official ruled out sending ground troops to Syria or implementing a no-fly zone","depth":6},{"id":128,"text":"to blunt al-Assad 's aerial superiority over rebels","depth":7},{"id":129,"text":"fighting to oust his regime .","depth":7},{"id":130,"text":"The official insisted","depth":6},{"id":131,"text":"that all other options were under consideration by Obama","depth":7},{"id":132,"text":"but put no time frame on a decision .","depth":7},{"id":133,"text":"Meanwhile , a senior Defense Department official told CNN 's Chris Lawrence Monday","depth":7},{"id":134,"text":"that four U.S. Navy destroyers `` maintain readiness","depth":8},{"id":135,"text":"and ,","depth":10},{"id":136,"text":"if required ,","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"could execute a mission within hours ''","depth":11},{"id":138,"text":"of being ordered to do so .","depth":9},{"id":139,"text":"But the official added","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"that the U.S. military remained `` in a holding pattern ''","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"as Obama considers both military and nonmilitary options .","depth":8},{"id":142,"text":"Also , Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel said","depth":8},{"id":143,"text":"while visiting Indonesia","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"that any U.S. action `` will be in concert with the international community and within the framework of legal justification . ''","depth":7},{"id":145,"text":"While U.N. Secretary-General Ban Ki-moon said Monday","depth":10},{"id":146,"text":"that the use of chemical weapons was a crime against humanity","depth":11},{"id":147,"text":"and must be punished ,","depth":11},{"id":148,"text":"certain opposition by Syrian ally Russia and possibly China undermined the possibility","depth":10},{"id":149,"text":"that the Security Council would support a military mission .","depth":10},{"id":150,"text":"Instead , a limited coalition of NATO partners such as Germany , France and Britain","depth":11},{"id":151,"text":"-- all of which have called for action against Syria --","depth":11},{"id":152,"text":"and some Arab League members appeared more likely to provide the political backing","depth":11},{"id":153,"text":"needed by Obama","depth":12},{"id":154,"text":"to order U.S. missile strikes .","depth":12},{"id":155,"text":"A senior administration official told CNN on Monday","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"that the goals of any coalition military action would be to punish al-Assad","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"and show him","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"that there was a cost","depth":15},{"id":159,"text":"for using chemical weapons","depth":15},{"id":160,"text":"while preventing him from doing so again .","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"In addition , a military strike would seek to degrade the Syrian regime 's capabilities enough","depth":12},{"id":162,"text":"to weaken it","depth":13},{"id":163,"text":"without causing it to fall to an opposition","depth":14},{"id":164,"text":"considered unprepared to assume power ,","depth":14},{"id":165,"text":"the official said .","depth":11},{"id":166,"text":"Possible coalition partners include NATO allies Britain , France , Germany and Canada , as well as regional powers Qatar , Turkey , Saudi Arabia and the United Arab Emirates .","depth":7},{"id":167,"text":"Last month , Joint Chiefs Chairman Gen. Martin Dempsey provided Congress with a list of declassified U.S. military options for Syria","depth":7},{"id":168,"text":"that emphasized the high costs and risks of what he said","depth":8},{"id":169,"text":"would amount to `` an act of war '' at a time of deep budget cuts .","depth":8},{"id":170,"text":"Dempsey 's letter ,","depth":9},{"id":171,"text":"dated July 19 ,","depth":9},{"id":172,"text":"listed U.S. assets in the region","depth":8},{"id":173,"text":"including Patriot missile defense batteries in Turkey and Jordan , as well as F-16 jet fighters","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"positioned","depth":9},{"id":175,"text":"to defend Jordan from possible cross-border trouble .","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"In addition , the Pentagon has sent four warships","depth":7},{"id":177,"text":"armed with cruise missiles to the region .","depth":7},{"id":178,"text":"According to U.S. officials ,","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"updated options","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"offered the president in recent days","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"included :","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"- Cruise missiles","depth":11},{"id":183,"text":"fired from one of four Navy destroyers","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"deployed in the Mediterranean Sea .","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"The missiles would be used","depth":11},{"id":186,"text":"to strike `` command and control '' facilities such as command bunkers , or the Syrian regime 's means","depth":14},{"id":187,"text":"of delivering chemical weapons :","depth":14},{"id":188,"text":"artillery batteries and launchers .","depth":13},{"id":189,"text":"There is no indication","depth":13},{"id":190,"text":"that the missiles would strike at actual chemical weapons stockpiles .","depth":13},{"id":191,"text":"- Military jets","depth":11},{"id":192,"text":"firings weapons from outside Syrian airspace .","depth":11},{"id":193,"text":"This option carries additional risks","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"and is considered less likely .","depth":11},{"id":195,"text":"`` They have to be careful to do this in concert with our allies , ''","depth":10},{"id":196,"text":"Democratic Rep. Adam Schiff of California , a member of the House Intelligence Committee , told CNN on Sunday ,","depth":10},{"id":197,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":198,"text":"that","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"`` I do n't think","depth":14},{"id":200,"text":"the White House is going to want to risk American lives","depth":15},{"id":201,"text":"by sending pilots over Syria ,","depth":15},{"id":202,"text":"so that really limits our options to cruise strikes","depth":13},{"id":203,"text":"and think","depth":13},{"id":204,"text":"that 's probably where the White House is going to go . '","depth":13},{"id":205,"text":"' Cruise missile strikes could be `` very punishing '' on al-Assad 's missile supplies and aircraft","depth":10},{"id":206,"text":"without going after the chemical weapons stockpiles","depth":11},{"id":207,"text":"to risk dispersing them ,","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"Schiff said .","depth":9},{"id":209,"text":"To Aaron David Miller , a vice president at the Woodrow Wilson International Center , the situation is forcing Obama to shift from being an `` avoider-in-chief '' regarding military involvement in Syria .","depth":5},{"id":210,"text":"`` It 's almost inevitable that the president will authorize some form of military action , ''","depth":8},{"id":211,"text":"Miller told National Public Radio in an interview","depth":9},{"id":212,"text":"broadcast Monday .","depth":9},{"id":213,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":214,"text":"he expected a significant response","depth":9},{"id":215,"text":"that amounts to `` a warning","depth":12},{"id":216,"text":"that lays down this time a red line","depth":13},{"id":217,"text":"that the president intends to enforce ,","depth":14},{"id":218,"text":"not one","depth":15},{"id":219,"text":"that turns pink . ''","depth":15},{"id":220,"text":"`` It can not simply be a couple of cruise missiles into a storage shed somewhere , ''","depth":12},{"id":221,"text":"Miller said ,","depth":12},{"id":222,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":223,"text":"that the goal was to deter al-Assad","depth":12},{"id":224,"text":"rather than topple him","depth":13},{"id":225,"text":"or radically shift the balance in Syria at this time .","depth":13},{"id":226,"text":"`` The president 's not on the verge","depth":8},{"id":227,"text":"of becoming the cavalry","depth":9},{"id":228,"text":"to rescue the country . ''","depth":9},{"id":229,"text":"Schiff agreed","depth":9},{"id":230,"text":"that Obama has little choice","depth":10},{"id":231,"text":"but to respond strongly .","depth":10},{"id":232,"text":"`` In terms of the credibility of the White House , ''","depth":10},{"id":233,"text":"he said ,","depth":10},{"id":234,"text":"`` the cost","depth":12},{"id":235,"text":"of not acting now ,","depth":12},{"id":236,"text":"I think ,","depth":11},{"id":237,"text":"exceeds the cost","depth":11},{"id":238,"text":"of acting . ''","depth":11}],"relations":[{"parent":477,"left":0,"right":476,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":476,"left":364,"right":475,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":364,"left":245,"right":363,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":245,"left":240,"right":244,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":240,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":244,"left":243,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":243,"left":241,"right":242,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":24